 The broadcaster announced Maijang s resignation in a statement released on Wednesday. It is indeed a bittersweet moment for us as the SABC. His departure comes at an exciting time for us as we are starting to see the fruits of our repositioning as a division a project that Mr. Mpherwane contributed immensely to SABC TV group executive Nomsa Philiso said in a statement.Maijang was general manager of TV Bouquet and headed up the management of SABC 1 2 3 and Encore at the time of his resignation.The SABC has confirmed it would start the recruitment process to find Maijang s replacement immediately.